.TH HSH 1 "April 2026" "1.1" "Simple Shell Manual"

.SH NAME
hsh - simple UNIX command interpreter

.SH SYNOPSIS
.B hsh

.SH DESCRIPTION
.B hsh
is a simple UNIX command line interpreter written in C.

It reads commands from standard input, parses them, resolves executable paths, creates child processes, and executes programs.

The shell works in both interactive and non-interactive modes.

.SH HOW IT WORKS
The shell follows a command processing cycle:
.PP
read -> parse -> resolve -> fork -> execve -> wait -> repeat

.SH COMMANDS
The shell executes commands entered by the user.

Commands may be:
.TP
.B External commands
Programs located using the PATH environment variable.
.TP
.B Built-in commands
Commands implemented directly in the shell.

.SH BUILTINS
The following built-in commands are supported:
.TP
.B exit
Exit the shell.
.TP
.B env
Print the current environment variables.

.SH ENVIRONMENT
The shell uses environment variables, especially:
.TP
.B PATH
Used to locate executable programs.

.SH EXIT STATUS
The shell returns 0 on success and non-zero on failure.

.SH LIMITATIONS
This shell does not support:
.PP
Pipes, redirections, command chaining, background execution, quoting, or wildcards.

